'''Owari no Kuni Fudoki''' (尾張国風土記) was the [[Fudoki]] of {{ill|Owari Province|ja|尾張国|qq=draft}}, compiled during the [[Nara period]]. The full text does not survive, and only a few fragments ({{ill|fragments|ja|逸文|qq=draft}}) are preserved through later sources.
== Overview == The ''Fudoki of Owari Province'' was compiled in the early [[8th century]]. Like other extant Fudoki, it likely recorded local place names and traditions. However, much of the text was lost by the Edo period. The fragments now available are citations in later works such as {{ill|Shaku Nihongi|ja|釈日本紀|qq=draft}}, {{ill|Chinbukuro|ja|塵袋|qq=draft}}, and {{ill|Man'yōshū Commentary|ja|万葉集註釈|qq=draft}}{{Sfn|Kurita Kan|1927|pp=47-58}}.
