=== Kawashima Shrine === {{Quotation| Kawashima Shrine: Located in Kawashima Village of Kawanuma Township, Hakuri District. During the reign of Emperor Shōmu, it was reported by Omikumi no Oshihito that the deity appeared as a white deer. The Emperor issued a decree to enshrine the deity as a heavenly shrine.{{Sfn|Kurita Kan|1927|p=50}} |''Man'yōshū Commentary,'' Volume 1}}
This fragment concerns {{ill|Kawashima Shrine (Kōnan City)|ja|川島神社|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Kawashima Shrine (Kōnan City)|qq=|1=Kawashima Shrine (Kōnan City)|comment=changed title based on wikidata|WD=Q16766691}} in Hakuri District. It recounts the shrine's establishment during the reign of Emperor Shōmu after a divine manifestation{{Sfn|Kurita Kan|1927|p=50}}.
